# Lift session state above conditional views

State that must survive in-app navigation (chat history, drafts, selections, scroll
position) must NOT live inside a component that is conditionally mounted/unmounted by a
router or tab switch. Unmounting destroys `useState`, silently wiping the data.

1. **Own session state in an always-mounted shell.** Hold it in the layout/`AppContent`
   component (or a Context provider) that stays mounted across route/tab changes, and pass
   it into the view (e.g. `<ChatPanel chat={chat} />`).
2. **Conditional render = unmount.** `cond ? <A/> : <B/>` and route switches unmount the
   hidden branch. Anything its hooks held is gone on return — do not rely on it persisting.
3. **Components stay reusable.** Prefer an optional prop with a local fallback
   (`chat ?? useChatHistory()`) so the component still works standalone and in unit tests.
   Always call the hook unconditionally (rules of hooks).
4. **ADR-004:** Vecinita chat history is client-side-only — lift it within the SPA only;
   never persist it to the server or to storage that leaves the browser.

